# Movie Ticket Booking System (FastAPI)

## Project Description
This is a backend application built using FastAPI that simulates a real-world movie ticket booking system.  
It allows users to view movies, book tickets, apply discounts, and manage seat availability.

# Features Implemented

# Day 1 — Basic APIs
- Home route (`GET /`)
- Get all movies (`GET /movies`)
- Get movie by ID (`GET /movies/{movie_id}`)
- Movies summary (`GET /movies/summary`)

# Day 2 & 3 — POST + Validation + Helpers
- Booking tickets (`POST /bookings`)
- Pydantic validation for request body
- Helper functions:
  - `find_movie()`
  - `calculate_ticket_cost()`
- Promo codes:
  - SAVE10 → 10% discount
  - SAVE20 → 20% discount

# Day 4 — CRUD Operations
- Add new movie (`POST /movies`)
- Update movie (`PUT /movies/{movie_id}`)
- Delete movie (`DELETE /movies/{movie_id}`)

# Day 5 — Multi-Step Workflow
- Seat Hold (`POST /seat-hold`)
- Confirm Booking (`POST /seat-confirm/{hold_id}`)
- Release Hold (`DELETE /seat-release/{hold_id}`)

# Day 6 — Advanced APIs
- Search movies (`GET /movies/search`)
- Sort movies (`GET /movies/sort`)
- Pagination (`GET /movies/page`)
- Combined browsing (`GET /movies/browse`)

# Tech Stack
- Python
- FastAPI
- Uvicorn

# How to Run the Project
1. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m uvicorn main:app --reload